</p><textarea readonly="" accesskey="," id="wpTextbox1" cols="80" rows="25" style="" class="mw-editfont-monospace" lang="en" dir="ltr" name="wpTextbox1">Below follows a list of mutations, for a more advanced enquiry about mutations click [[mutation|here]]

== Categories ==
Once a mutation is selected, you will begin to mutate towards it. If any mutations you currently have conflict with this mutation, then one of the conflicting mutations is randomly removed. If you have no conflicting mutations, but don't have any of the prerequisites, you will begin to mutate towards a random prerequisite. If you already have a prerequisite mutation and no conflicting mutations, you gain the selected mutation immediately.

Starting [[traits]] do not increase respective category strength, unless you gain them later via actual mutation! On the upside, this does mean that you can take Robust Genetics without placing yourself into the rather undesirable slime category.

== Basic traits ==
Starting traits can sometimes be gained (or rarely lost) through mutation; if you gain one via mutation, you can lose it as normal.  If you start with one of them, Purifier will attempt to set you back to it should it be changed.

As with all mutations, they can jump out as part of your evolution to a further mutation (if this further mutation is rolled too early and cannot be gained by itself), or as part of mutation category-enforcement.

See the bottom of the page for a full list of [[Traits]].

Some traits you can only get at character creation, these represent the professional training the character got before the cataclysm occurred. These give unique minor bonuses.

== Mutation-only traits ==
In addition to a points value, mutations have a visibility value and an ugliness value. Positive visibility means that the mutation is prominent. This will visibly identify the player as a mutant, resulting in discrimination from mutant-haters and trust with mutants/mutant-lovers. Positive ugliness means that the mutation is grotesque.  This will result in a negative reaction from [[NPC]]s, even those who are themselves mutated, unless the NPC is a mutant-lover.

== Special ==
There are two (one? all?) secret mutation thresholds. Here are some hints to get us searching.

{{trait|MARLOSS|Marloss Carrier|0|0|0}}
{{trait|MYCUS|Mycus|0|0|0}}

They cannot be gained through random mutation at all. [[Marloss Berry|This link spoils it all.]]

